reviews.text: Its only advantage is a delectable countryside location. On the other hand, there is sod-all  here for a long way in all directions. The village is far away down a road which is dangerous to walk, the parking is poor and there never has been a pub or shop here. If this were anywhere else but Surrey, Beeching would have got rid of it.

Absolutely superb station - beautiful, though not the most unique that the British Rail system has to offer. Used by approximately 32,000 people a year this really shows, with the whole station feeling almost abandoned. I have no problem with the grime in the underpass, as this only made my experience here all the more exciting. With cargo trains frequently passing through and an awesome location to top it all off, this is a must-visit station.
An attractive traditional railway station on the scenic Mole Valley Line. Steam trains pass through occasionally.
